#. Tag: title
#: man-kate.1.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "Description"
msgstr "वर्णनम्‌"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kate; is the &kde; Advanced Text Editor."
msgstr "&कते; इति &kde; उन्नत पाठ सम्पादक।"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kate; also provides the editor part for various applications, under the "
"name &kwrite;."
msgstr ""
"&कते; विभिन्नानां अनुप्रयोगानाम् कृते सम्पादकभागं अपि प्रदाति, &kwrite; इति नाम्ना ।"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some of &kate;'s many features include configurable syntax highlighting for "
"languages ranging from C and C++ to &HTML; to bash scripts, the ability to "
"create and maintain projects, a multiple document interface (<acronym>MDI</"
"acronym>), and a self-contained terminal emulator."
msgstr ""
"&kate; इत्यस्य अनेकविशेषतासु केषुचित् C तथा C++ तः &HTML; स्क्रिप्ट्-इत्यस्य bash-करणाय, "
"परियोजना-निर्माणस्य, परिपालनस्य च क्षमता, बहुविध-दस्तावेज-अन्तरफलकं (<acronym>MDI</"
"acronym>), स्वयमेव समाहितं टर्मिनल्-अनुकरणकं च ।"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"But &kate; is more than a programmer's editor. Its ability to open several "
"files at once makes it ideal for editing &UNIX;'s many configuration files. "
"This document was written in &kate;."
msgstr ""
"किन्तु &कते; प्रोग्रामरस्य सम्पादकात् अधिकं भवति । एकदा एव अनेकसञ्चिकाः उद्घाटयितुं अस्य "
"क्षमता &UNIX;इत्यस्य अनेकविन्याससञ्चिकानां सम्पादनार्थं आदर्शं करोति । एतत् दस्तावेजं &kate;."

#. Tag: title
#: man-kate.1.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid "Options"
msgstr "विकल्पाः"

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>-s</option>, <option>--start</option> <replaceable>name</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<option value=-s>-s</option> , ९.<option value=--start> --प्रारंभः</"
"option><replaceable> नामः</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start &kate; with a given session."
msgstr "आरभत &kate; दत्तसत्रेण सह ।"

#. Tag: option
#: man-kate.1.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "--startanon"
msgstr "--स्टारतानोन्"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start &kate; with a new anonymous session, implies <option>-n</option>."
msgstr ""
"आरभत &amp;kate; नूतनेन अनामिकसत्रेण सह, तात्पर्यम्<option value=-n> -न</option> ."

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-n</option>, <option>--new</option>"
msgstr "<option value=-n>-न</option> , ९.<option value=--new> --नूतनम्‌</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:82
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Force start of a new &kate; instance (is ignored if <option>start</option> "
"is used and another &kate; instance already has the given session opened), "
"forced if no parameters and no URLs are given at all."
msgstr ""
"एकस्य नूतनस्य &amp;kate; उदाहरणम् (उपेक्षितं भवति यदि<option value=start> प्रारंभः</"
"option> प्रयुज्यते च अन्यः &amp;कते; instance इत्यनेन पूर्वमेव दत्तं सत्रं उद्घाटितम् अस्ति), "
"यदि कोऽपि पैरामीटर् नास्ति तथा च कोऽपि URL सर्वथा न दत्तः तर्हि बाध्यः ।"

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-b</option>, <option>--block</option>"
msgstr ""
"<option value=-b>-ख</option> , ९.<option value=--block> --मृदुवस्तु</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If using an already running &kate; instance, block until it exits, if URLs "
"given to open."
msgstr ""
"यदि पूर्वमेव चालितं &kate; instance, block यावत् न निर्गच्छति, यदि URLs उद्घाटयितुं "
"दत्ताः सन्ति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:92
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-p, --pid</option> <replaceable> pid</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<option value=\"-p, --pid\">-प, --पिड्</option><replaceable> पिड</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:94
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only try to reuse kate instance with this <replaceable>pid</replaceable> (is "
"ignored if <option>start</option> is used and another &kate; instance "
"already has the given session opened)."
msgstr ""
"केवलं एतेन सह kate instance इत्यस्य पुनः उपयोगं कर्तुं प्रयतध्वम्<replaceable> पिड</"
"replaceable> (उपेक्ष्यते यदि<option value=start> प्रारंभः</option> प्रयुज्यते च अन्यः "
"&amp;कते; instance इत्यनेन पूर्वमेव दत्तं सत्रं उद्घाटितम् अस्ति)।"

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:99
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-e, --encoding</option> <replaceable> name</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<option value=\"-e, --encoding\">-ई, --एन्कोडिंग्</option><replaceable> नामः</"
"replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set encoding for the file to open."
msgstr "सञ्चिकायाः उद्घाटनार्थं एन्कोडिंग् सेट् कुर्वन्तु ।"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use this to force a file opened in utf-8 format, for instance. (The "
"command <command>iconv -l</command> provides a list of encodings, which may "
"be helpful to you.)"
msgstr ""
"भवन्तः एतत् उपयोक्तुं शक्नुवन्ति यत् utf-8 प्रारूपेण उद्घाटितां सञ्चिकां बाध्यं कर्तुं शक्नुवन्ति, "
"उदाहरणार्थम् । (<command>iconv -l</command> इति आदेशः एन्कोडिंग्-सूचीं प्रदाति, यत् "
"भवतः कृते सहायकं भवितुम् अर्हति ।)"

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-l, --line</option> <replaceable> line</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<option value=\"-l, --line\">-ल, --रेखा</option><replaceable> पंक्ति</"
"replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid "Navigate to this line."
msgstr "अस्याः पङ्क्तौ गच्छन्तु ।"

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-c, --column</option> <replaceable> column</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<option value=\"-c, --column\">-ग, --स्तम्भ</option><replaceable> स्तम्भ:</"
"replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid "Navigate to this column."
msgstr "अस्मिन् स्तम्भे गच्छन्तु ।"

#. Tag: option
#: man-kate.1.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "-i, --stdin"
msgstr "-इ, --स्तदिन्"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid "Read the contents of <filename>stdin</filename>."
msgstr "<filename>stdin</filename> इत्यस्य विषयवस्तु पठन्तु ।"

#. Tag: option
#: man-kate.1.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid "--tempfile"
msgstr "--tempfile इति"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "The files/&URL;s opened by the application will be deleted after use."
msgstr "अनुप्रयोगेन उद्घाटिताः सञ्चिकाः/&URL;s उपयोगानन्तरं विलोपिताः भविष्यन्ति ।"

#. Tag: replaceable
#: man-kate.1.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid "file"
msgstr "सञ्चिका"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "File to open."
msgstr "सञ्चिकां उद्घाटयितुं।"

#. Tag: title
#: man-kate.1.docbook:134
#, no-c-format
msgid "See Also"
msgstr "इदमपि पश्यन्तु"

#. Tag: member
#: man-kate.1.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"More detailed user documentation is available from <ulink url=\"help:/kate"
"\">help:/kate</ulink> (either enter this &URL; into &konqueror;, or run "
"<userinput><command>khelpcenter</command> <parameter>help:/kate</parameter></"
"userinput>)."
msgstr ""
"अधिकविस्तृतं उपयोक्तृदस्तावेजं <ulink url=\"help:/kate\">help:/kate</ulink> इत्यस्मात् "
"उपलभ्यते (एतत् &URL; &konqueror; मध्ये प्रविशन्तु, अथवा "
"<userinput><command>khelpcenter</command> < चालयन्तु पैरामीटर>सहाय्यम्:/kate</"
"parameter></userinput>)।"

#. Tag: member
#: man-kate.1.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid "kf6options(7)"
msgstr "kf6विकल्पाः(7) ."

#. Tag: member
#: man-kate.1.docbook:142
#, no-c-format
msgid "qt6options(7)"
msgstr "qt6विकल्प(7) 1.1."

#. Tag: member
#: man-kate.1.docbook:143
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There is also further information available at the <ulink url=\"https://kate-"
"editor.org/\">&kate; website</ulink>."
msgstr "<ulink url=\"https://kate-editor.org/\">&kate; जालपुट</ulink>।"

#. Tag: title
#: man-kate.1.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid "Examples"
msgstr "उदाहरणानि"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To open a file named <filename>source.cpp</filename> at column 15, line 25, "
"in an existing &kate; window, you could use:"
msgstr "विद्यमानस्य &kate; window, भवान् उपयोक्तुं शक्नोति स्म:"

#. Tag: screen
#: man-kate.1.docbook:153
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput><command>kate</command> <option>-c 15</option> <option>-l 25</"
"option> <filename>source.cpp</filename></userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput><command>कते</command><option value=\"-c 15\"> -ग 15</"
"option><option value=\"-l 25\"> -l 25</option><filename> स्रोतः.cpp</"
"filename></userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have an active internet connection, you can take advantage of &kde;'s "
"network transparency to open a file from an &FTP; site. If you do not have "
"write permission on the remote server, the file will be opened read only and "
"you will be prompted for a local filename to save to if you make changes. If "
"you do have write permission, changes will be saved transparently over the "
"network."
msgstr ""
"यदि भवतां सक्रियः अन्तर्जालसम्पर्कः अस्ति तर्हि &FTP; क्षेत्र। यदि भवतां दूरस्थसर्वरस्य "
"लेखनस्य अनुमतिः नास्ति तर्हि सञ्चिका केवलं पठनीयरूपेण उद्घाटिता भविष्यति तथा च यदि भवान् "
"परिवर्तनं करोति तर्हि तस्मिन् रक्षितुं स्थानीयसञ्चिकानाम प्रार्थयिष्यते । यदि भवतां समीपे "
"लेखनस्य अनुमतिः अस्ति तर्हि परिवर्तनं जालपुटेन पारदर्शकरूपेण रक्षितं भविष्यति ।"

#. Tag: screen
#: man-kate.1.docbook:161
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput><command>kate</command> <option><replaceable>&kde-ftp;README</"
"replaceable></option></userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput><command>केट्</command><option><replaceable> &amp;kde-ftp;पठ्ठे</"
"replaceable></option></userinput>"

#. Tag: title
#: man-kate.1.docbook:179
#, no-c-format
msgid "Authors"
msgstr "लेखकाः"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:180
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The maintainer of &kate; is &Christoph.Cullmann; &Christoph.Cullmann.mail;. "
"A comprehensive list of authors and contributors is available in the "
"complete user manual mentioned above."
msgstr ""
"पालकः &kate; is &Christoph.Cullmann; &क्रिस्टोफ.कुलमैन.मेल;. लेखकानां योगदातृणां च "
"व्यापकसूची उपरि उल्लिखिते सम्पूर्णे उपयोक्तृपुस्तिकायां उपलभ्यते ।"
